Who has not played Cut the Rope? If you own a smartphone, chances are you have fed the little green creature a couple of times by now. If you have not, you have 10 seconds to do so. Seriously, this is one of the best games out there, and it would be a shame if you missed it. But what is Cut the Rope anyway, and why I am praising it so much? Well, Cut the Rope is a physics-based puzzle game that tasks you, the player, with feeding a little green creature that goes by the name of Om Nom. To achieve this, you will have to cut lots and lots of ropes while making use of all the devices and objects set-up in each level. Speaking of levels, each one is self-contained making the game very easy to pick up and play. The game has been downloaded by 1.000.000 users, so the quality speaks for itself.

Using Root Explorer, mount R-W and navigate to /data/data/com.zeptolab.ctr.paid/files/shared_prefs. Rename the "com.zeptolab.ctr.CtrApp.xml" file (i.e., create a backup of your new all-zeroes score file) and make a copy of the "CtrAppPaid.xml" file (your old scores file). Then, rename the original "CtrAppPaid.xml" file to "com.zeptolab.ctr.CtrApp.xml". That's it...you should see all your old scores now. If you have enough stars the new box will be unlocked.
